         <abstract>
            <p>We show that for any prime number &lt;latex&gt;$l &gt; 2$&lt;/latex&gt; the minus class group of the field of the l-th roots of unity &lt;tex-math&gt;$\overline{Q_p}(\zeta_l$&lt;/tex-math&gt;) admits a finite free resolution of length 1 as a module over the ring &lt;tex-math&gt;$\widehat{\mathbf Z}[G]/ (1 + \iota$&lt;/tex-math&gt;). Here ι denotes complex conjugation in G = Gal(&lt;tex-math&gt;$\overline{Q_p}(\zeta_l)/\overline{Q_p}) \cong (\mathbf{Z}/l\mathbf{Z})^*$&lt;/tex-math&gt;. Moreover, for the primes l ≤ 509 we show that the minus class group is cyclic as a module over this ring. For these primes we also determine the structure of the minus class group.</p>
          </abstract>
